Package: locatr
Title: Audit-Ready Geocoding and Local Geography Crosswalks for Messy Location Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("George", "Arthur", , "prigasgenthian48@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-1975-1459"))
Description: A thin audit, validation, fallback, and crosswalk layer that sits on
    top of 'tidygeocoder'. It cleans and flags messy location addresses, geocodes
    them via the US Census batch geocoder with an ArcGIS fallback, validates the
    returned coordinates against a configurable bounding box (and optionally a
    true boundary polygon), joins points to local geography with 'sf', supports
    manual overrides, and exports a dashboard-ready crosswalk. Every step records
    an audit trail so a reviewer can see how each coordinate was produced.
